<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="1.0">Long ago, and to great fanfare, business tycoon Milton Hershey revealed that he had given away his world-famous chocolate company, a gift to the school for poor orphans that he had founded with his wife.</p>
        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="2.0">“Well, I have no children — that is, no heirs,” he said in 1923. “So I decided to make the orphan boys of the United States my heirs.”</p>
        
    
                        


   
            
